# Jetson Git & Runtime Ops

## Source of truth

- **Runtime + `git push`:** Jetson (`zipline@10.0.0.15`, `~/tiltytable`)
- **Mac:** fine for editing/fetch; **cannot push** (DoorDash DLP blocks non-approved remotes)

## Remotes (Jetson)

```text
origin  git@github.com:TiltyTable/tiltytable.git
jerry   git@github.com:lijerryli/tiltytable.git   # leave alone; do not delete
```

- Authorship on Jetson: `TiltyTable <tiltytable@users.noreply.github.com>`
- Never commit as a personal name/email for this project.

## rsync / sync pitfalls

- When syncing Mac → Jetson, **exclude `.git/`** (or only sync specific paths).
- Copying Mac `.git` overwrites Jetson remotes with `github-personal:` (broken on Jetson).
- After any full-tree sync, verify: `git remote -v` and `ssh -T git@github.com`.

## Before pushing

1. Confirm on Jetson: `git remote get-url origin` is `git@github.com:TiltyTable/tiltytable.git`
2. `git push origin main` from the Jetson, not the Mac
